node.text: I made a video of how I told Cole  and our friends & family that I was pregnant! I found out in the morning before when we were getting ready for the beach and totally thought the test was going to be negative. I was shocked when it said positive and had Knox run the test out to Cole! I still can’t believe our little family is growing ✨

node.title: So much love for this little babe already👶🏼💛

node.text: Watching you become a dad has been my most favorite thing. Fatherhood comes to effortlessly and naturally to you and it’s really amazing to see you in action. You are nurturing, playful, loving, selfless and all in. I could not ask for a better husband and daddy to my future babies.

node.title: Happy Fathers Day to the best dad 💙

node.text:
“ A​ Roadmap To Using Instagram To Grow Your Business”. My passion project I have been working on for months is finally here! This course was created for small business owners, service based brands, and influencers. I wanted to help others follow their dreams and turn their passions into profits! There are 12 Modules covering everything from growth, working with brands, finding a niche, smarter working strategies, launching digital products, and expanding to other social media platforms. But, that’s not all:⁣

node.text:
These are pantry friendly, kid friendly, refined sugar/ flour free and DELICIOUS! I came up with this recipe a few weeks ago when I needed something to keep us all full on a 10 hour flight. Knox loves them and even got his first little taste of chocolate yesterday because I forgot to to make few without chocolate chips 🙈 Make extra and bring them to family/ friends to let them know you’re thinking of them 💛 Save this post for future reference & share it with a friend! I want to make more recipe videos and next time I’m thinking a dinner meal! Comment what recipes you want to see below 👇🏽 ⁣
*Makes 12 Muffins* ⁣
Ingredients:⁣
- 2 cups oat flour ⁣
- 2 eggs⁣
- 1/3 cup coconut oil ⁣
- 1/3 cup pure maple syrup (or honey) ⁣
- 1 cup mashed bananas⁣
- 1/4 cup milk ( I use almond or oat milk)⁣
- 1 tsp. baking soda⁣
- 1 tsp. Vanilla ⁣
- 1/2 tsp. Sea salt ⁣
- 1 tsp. cinnamon ⁣
- 1/3 cup chopped pecans ⁣
-1/4 cup chocolate chips ⁣
⁣
Directions: ⁣
- Preheat the oven to 325 (162 Celsius)⁣
- Scoop 2 cups of organic oats into a blender. Blend until it is the consistency of flour ⁣
- Mix together all of the ingredients and pour the batter into a greased muffin tin.⁣
- Bake for 20-22 minutes and enjoy!⁣
⁣
Xo, Maddie 
Sound: Bound 2 Instrumental

node.text:
The perfect blend of sweet, tangy and delicious🌟 My neighbor brought over some fresh lilikoi from her tree and I threw this together! If ya wanna try it out here’s the recipe:
•4 lilikoi (seeds included) • 1 frozen banana (I ran out of frozen ones but it will make the smoothie thicker)
• 1 cup of frozen mango
• 1 cup of frozen peach •1 cup of frozen strawberry • splash of nut milk 
Top with homemade granola, fresh strawberries, banana, more lilikoi, coconut or whatever you’d like! 🍓🥥
We’re also got the product samples in for our shop launching in the New Year 🙌🏽 Any guesses what products from the video we might be releasing?! I am blown away by how this community has grown over the years! This all started while I was a college student trying to create a healthier lifestyle for myself. I never could’ve dreamed I would get the opportunity to connect with all of you from around the world! THANK YOU! I’ll be sending my smoothie ebook to a few of you who comment 💛

node.text: I’m showing you what our typical grocery haul looks like each month! This is definitely one of our biggest because we hadn’t gone grocery shopping in over a month. We live an hour away from the nearest big super market so we typically do one big trip a month and then buy fruits and veggies from our local store in between trips 🥑🍉🍓🍍🍌#summerofwellness

node.text: The story of the day our little angel came into the the world 💙

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maddie Castellano on July 25, 2021 tagging @littleandfree. May be an image of 2 people, baby and indoor.

node.text:
Tell me you’re a parent without telling me you’re a parent. I’ll go first 🤪 I wipe pee off me like it’s water, sing cocomelon in the shower, and haven’t set an alarm clock in years.⁣
This pic of the boys in their matching @littleandfree outfits is one of my new favs 🥰 The fabric is insanely comfortable, stretchy and durable. They have amazing basics for both babies and toddlers that are designed by moms, for moms! We are partnering up to give two winners $100 store credit to their shop! All you have to do to enter is follow @littleandfree , like this photo and comment below!⁣
*US Only. Winner will he announced next week*

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maddie Castellano in Muir Woods, San Francisco. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing, footwear and outdoors.

node.text: Knox in his element with dirt on his face and his Lightning McQueen car glued to his hand! When he was saying prayers last night he went freestyle and starting thanking God for things all on his own. He said “Thank you peacocks, trash trucks, hot tubbing, trees, mommy, daddy, Zo Zo, moon, rocks, and big rocks”. It was such a silly and simple moment,  it also one that made me so proud. I love that he has learned to appreciate even the smallest things in life.

node.text: 5 years of marriage in 30 seconds ✨ I got a little emo making this video seeing how much good has come out of our love. It’s a perfect reminder to always make our relationship the number one priority. You’re still the one 🤍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maddie Castellano on July 22, 2021 tagging @kyleepatterson, and @cole_castellano. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, flower and outdoors.

node.text: 5 years of us. It’s impossible to put into words what you mean to me since our love is my greatest treasure. It’s been amazing watching our relationship grow and evolve over the last 5 years. We were both just kids who didn’t know much, but we knew we needed eachother. You still look at me the same way you did on our wedding day and make me feel wanted every single day. I can’t wait to see what else life has in store for us. Happy anniversary, Cole, I love you more than you’ll ever know 🤍

node.text: Knox is now taking hair appointments if you’re interested 😜 Also swipe to see Enzo’s cheesy smile and belly because his shirts too small (he’s just so dang long) 😂 My go to look this summer has been the beachy waves! It’s one of my fav ways to style my hair and only takes 15 minutes! I’ve been using the @bondiboost Wave Wand for over a year now and it’s by far the best I’ve used. It rarely goes on sale so I was so stoked when they gave me a code to share with all of you! Use the code MADDIECASTELLANO20 for 20% off at checkout!

node.text: Motherhood is hard. Harder than I expected. It’s pushing a double stroller up switchbacks, nursing crouching over a car seat on the freeway, hiking in shorts covered in baby poop ,and peeing in a cup while driving so you don’t wake up the kids kind of hard 😂 But there is truly nothing I would rather be doing. Cole and I were reminiscing about how easy and fun traveling used to be before we had kids. Of course there are moments where I miss our spontaneous newlywed days, but if I had to choose between a life spent jetting off to a new country or one spent at home with my babies, you already know where you’d find me 🤍

node.text: We drove part of the Big Sur coast yesterday and it was everything I dreamed of and more 😍 It’s so surreal to see a place you have always imagined in real life. I also realized that Enzo looks like a friendly old man walking out to get the morning paper and now I can’t unsee it!!

node.text: Summer adventures with my people 🌼 We’re on our first ever family roadtrip and it’s been so much fun! In the 6 years Cole and I have been together, we’ve always lived on an island and never had a reason to roadtrip. We visited some family in Utah last week and now we’re driving up the California coast! I love making memories with my boys 🤍
